Add bounds checks for both utilization fields inside the existing `if k.Spec.Autoscaling != nil` block, after the MinReplicas checks and before the 'at least one metric' check:

```go
if k.Spec.Autoscaling.TargetCPUUtilization != nil {
    v := *k.Spec.Autoscaling.TargetCPUUtilization
    if v < 1 || v > 100 {
        allErrs = append(allErrs, field.Invalid(
            autoscalingPath.Child("targetCPUUtilization"),
            v,
            "targetCPUUtilization must be between 1 and 100",
        ))
    }
}
if k.Spec.Autoscaling.TargetMemoryUtilization != nil {
    v := *k.Spec.Autoscaling.TargetMemoryUtilization
    if v < 1 || v > 100 {
        allErrs = append(allErrs, field.Invalid(
            autoscalingPath.Child("targetMemoryUtilization"),
            v,
            "targetMemoryUtilization must be between 1 and 100",
        ))
    }
}
```
Also add corresponding unit tests: TestValidate_Autoscaling_Invalid_CPUUtilizationZero, TestValidate_Autoscaling_Invalid_CPUUtilizationExceeds100, TestValidate_Autoscaling_Invalid_MemoryUtilizationZero, TestValidate_Autoscaling_Invalid_MemoryUtilizationExceeds100.
